<b>Subject:</b> Re: Level differences in melee are too pronounced<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1715" TARGET=_self>Level differences in melee are too pronounced</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I did some tests and verified that the combat system is skewed a

<BR>&gt; bit too sharply IMO with just two levels of difference between
<BR>&gt; combatants.
<P>Tactics make a HUGE difference.
<P>A 6 Warrior will totally massacre a 4 Wizard in melee. But let the Wizard open the combat with something like Root, and then that 6 Warrior is going to be ina world of hurt.
<P>Melee isn't everything.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
